<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:03PM CDT  by NWS Eastern ND and Grand Forks</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Cavalier County through 430 PM CDT...
At 402 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Munich, or 21 miles west of Langdon, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Munich, Alsen and Calio.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
